asset.hookText: “Secrets of Louisville Chefs” Host Tim Laird puts the many uses of the KitchenAid maximum extraction juicer on display in his home kitchen. For more information about KitchenAid juicers, please visit: http://www.kitchenaid.com/countertop-appliances/juicers/.

transcripts: Tim Laird to the chef's corner with KitchenAid. Everyone knows I love to entertain especially with tools like this. It's the KitchenAid maximum extraction juicer. With this I can get more drinks with less prep work. It works with a patented two stage blade and auger system with a wide chute so you can turn just about any fruit or vegetable into a juice. Depending on which of the three pulp screens you use, you can get low pulp, high pulp, you can even use it to make sauces. Make healthy smoothies or add a fresh taste to your cocktails. I'm Tim Laird In the chef's corner with KitchenAid.
